# LinguaLeaf Cursor Rules

## Project Context
This is a React Native (Expo) language learning app with EPUB reader, translation, and vocabulary features.

## Code Style
- Follow AGENTS.md guidelines strictly
- TypeScript with strict mode
- Functional components with hooks
- Zustand for global state
- Centralized Supabase queries in queries.ts

## File Organization
- One component per file
- Co-locate types with usage
- Use @ alias for src imports
- Keep files under 200 lines

## Key Patterns
- Early returns for loading/error states
- Explicit error handling (no silent failures)
- Use theme tokens (never hardcode colors)
- Memoize expensive computations
- Log errors with logger utility

## Security
- Never expose service role key in client
- Trust RLS policies
- Validate user input
- Use signed URLs for private storage

## MVP Constraints
- iOS-first development
- Ship working over perfect
- Manual testing for MVP
- Defer non-essential features

